comment: LATR shows that Smart (BOS) makes contact with Jackson's (DET) body that affects his RSBQ and shot attempt.
Smart (BOS) makes incidental contact with Jackson (DET) that does not affect his RSBQ at the start of the drive.
Turner (BOS) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Johnson's (DET) driving shot attempt. Any contact on the play is initiated by Johnson.
Johnson (DET) extends his arm into Johnson (BOS), affecting his ability to defend the driving shot attempt.
Baynes (DET) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact that does not affect Johnson's (BOS) RSBQ or shot attempt.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Crowder (BOS) was the last player to touch the ball prior to it going OOB was overturned. Boston was awarded possession.
Morris (DET) grabs Thomas' (BOS) arm and affects his RSBQ on the drive.
Baynes (DET) sets the screen on Smart (BOS) and gives him room to avoid the contact.

Jackson (DET) makes incidental contact with Smart (BOS) that does not affect his layup attempt. Any additional incidental contact on the play occurs prior to possession by Smart and does not affect his ability to catch the pass.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Smart (BOS) was the last player to touch the ball prior to it going OOB was overturned. Boston was awarded possession.
Johnson (BOS) sets the screen on Caldwell-Pope (DET) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Morris (DET) pushes Smart (BOS) to the floor on a FT that was to remain in play. Since the FT attempt was successful, by rule the basket is scored and Smart is awarded one FT attempt.
Caldwell-Pope (DET) makes contact with Thomas' (BOS) non-shooting arm that affects his jump shot attempt.
Baynes (DET) sets the screen on Smart (BOS) and gives him room to avoid the contact. Smart does not go through the space of the screener as he attempts to fight through the screen.
Smart (BOS) clamps Baynes' (DET) arm and affects his ability to retrieve the rebound.
[Observable in enhanced video] Thomas (BOS) moves his pivot foot (right foot) at the start of his drive.
Olynyk (BOS) commits a take foul on Caldwell-Pope (DET).
Olynyk (BOS) is in a legal rebounding position and does not dislodge Baynes (DET).
